# Tannaka for stacks

https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/Tannaka+duality+for+geometric+stacks

A complete abelian tensor category is an abelian tensor category such that
  - it satisfies the axiom AB5 at additive and abelian categories;
  - (−)⊗x(-) \otimes x commutes with all small colimits.
      (equivalently, we have a closed monoidal category).
An abelian tensor category is called tame if for any short exact sequence
0→M′→M→M″→0 with M″ a flat object and any N∈C also the induced sequence
0→M′⊗N→M⊗N→M″⊗N→0 is exact.

Definition. For C,D two complete abelian tensor categories write
Func⊗(C,D)⊂Func(C,D)
for the core[=on restreint aux isos] of the subcategory of the functor category on those functors that
  - are symmetric monoidal functors;
  - commute with all small colimits (which implies they are additive and right exact)
  - preserve flat objects and short exact sequences whose last object is flat.
Write TCAbTens for the (strict) (2,1)-category of tame complete abelian tensor categories with hom-groupoids given by this Func_⊗.

Theorem. Let X be a geometric stack.
Then for every ring AA there is an equivalence of categories
RngdTopos(Sh((SpecA) et),Sh(X et))≃Hom⊗(QC(X),AMod)
hence (by the 2-Yoneda lemma)
X(SpecA)≃Hom⊗(QC(X),QC(SpecA)).
More generally, for (S,𝒪_S) any etale-locally ringed topos, we have
RngdTopos(S,Sh(X_et))≃Hom⊗(QC(X),𝒪 SMod).

Remark. It follows that forming quasicoherent sheaves constitutes a full and faithful (2,1)-functor QC:GeomStacks→TCAbTens^op from geometric stacks to tame complete abelian tensor categories.

